</node>
<node id="Lipohipertrofia">
  <data key="d0">Lipohipertrofia</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Lipohipertrofia refers to the formation of lumps or nodules in the skin due to repeated insulin injections.&lt;SEP&gt;Lipohypertrophy is a condition characterized by the formation of nodules or lumps in the skin, often as a result of repeated insulin injections in the same area.&lt;SEP&gt;Lipohipertrofia is a condition characterized by the accumulation of fat in localized areas, which can lead to insulin resistance and other complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-14a20edff579b0a517854d16cd546924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39d6a3c2463013fd9e732773c88b8db5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc0de9ad82a2e98af005736e04ca654d</data>
