<node id="Insulina">
  <data key="d0">Insulina</data>
  <data key="d1">product</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulina is a hormone used to regulate blood sugar levels in patients, particularly those with diabetes. It is produced by the pancreas and plays a crucial role in facilitating the entry of glucose into cells, thereby helping the body to absorb glucose from the blood and convert it into energy.

Insulina is administered via injection or pump, and its application requires proper technique to be effective. The medication is used to control blood sugar levels in individuals with diabetes, and its use is often necessary for patients who struggle to manage their condition through diet and exercise alone.

In addition to its role in regulating blood sugar levels, Insulina also helps to prevent the complications associated with diabetes, such as kidney damage and nerve damage. By controlling blood sugar levels, Insulina helps to reduce the risk of these complications and improve the overall health and well-being of patients with diabetes.

Insulina is a hormone that is essential for the proper functioning of the body's metabolic processes. It works by facilitating the entry of glucose into cells, which helps to regulate blood sugar levels and prevent the complications associated with diabetes. Insulina is a medication that is used to regulate blood sugar levels in individuals with diabetes, and its use is often necessary for patients who struggle to manage their condition through diet and exercise alone.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5b718276408c07c4ce95283bdfdf03de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03b2434384e8d28afce996ceb9caa794&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583c4afe8f20e09ec0157315dbab4992&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-14a20edff579b0a517854d16cd546924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e579d5ccfc0135f92c7582f294d15f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39d6a3c2463013fd9e732773c88b8db5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc0de9ad82a2e98af005736e04ca654d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84cbfc1493e013840892a69f8694a3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb55aa00a7f60f489e74950ed04d190b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768244577</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
