<edge source="Lipodistrofia" target="Lipo-hipertrofia">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Lipodistrofia is a condition that occurs when there is a change in the skin tissue where insulin is applied frequently, often leading to lipo-hipertrofia.</data>
  <data key="d9">insulin application,skin condition</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-5b718276408c07c4ce95283bdfdf03de</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1768244577</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Lipo-hipertrofia" target="Lipoatrofia">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Lipo-hipertrofia is a type of lipodistrofia where the skin becomes hardened and nodular due to the accumulation of fat in the area of insulin application, while lipoatrofia is a rare type where there is a loss of fat in the area.</data>
  <data key="d9">insulin application,skin condition</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-5b718276408c07c4ce95283bdfdf03de</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1768244577</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
